com.precog.client

Class QueryResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.precog.client.QueryResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<String>

    public class QueryResult
extends Object
implements Iterable<String>
    Result of the execution of a query (result set, errors, warnings, etc). If failed() is true, then you should assume that the data is invalid (though the partial result may still be of interest to you). A result has failed if either getErrors() is non-empty or getServerErrors() is non-empty.
    Author:
    Tom Switzer

    • Method Detail

      • failed

        public boolean failed()
        Returns true if the query did not execute successfully. This means that either there was an error with query itself (so getErrors() is non-empty), or there was a server error while executing the query (so getServerErrors() is non-empty).

      • succeeded

        public boolean succeeded()
        Returns true if the query executed successfully, otherwise returns false.

      • getErrors

        public List<TextTag> getErrors()
        Returns the list of errors found in the query. If there are no errors, then an empty list is returned.

      • getWarnings

        public List<TextTag> getWarnings()
        Returns the list of warnings for the query. If there are no warnings, then an empty list is returned.

      • getServerErrors

        public List<String> getServerErrors()
        Returns the list of server errors encountered while executing the query. If there are no errors, then an empty list is returned. If the list is non-empty, then that means there was a server error.
